en.expected_results:
Expected impacts are:
- Increase on the recollection and valorization of the Ocean Plastic Waste for its recycling and use on development of new materials;
- Reduction on the use of plastic based parts in the Maritime Industries, reducing the spillover of plastic into the Atlantic Ocean;
- Diversification of the economic activities linked to Green Growth by Maritime Industries by the introduction of 3DP and New Materials, bringing new market opportunities and jobs.

The expected results are: 
• Identify & share best practices in knowledge transfer (KT) & innovation, focusing on the role of Academia to foster cooperation between triple helix players; 
• Develop a Joint Action Plan to enhance KT & innovation capacity to foster Atlantic Area’s Blue Economy competitiveness at regional, interregional & transnational level; 
• Advance risk assessment and cost effectiveness tools to de-risk early stage technologies (EST); 
• Develop and share an operational tool to build capacity in Academia in KT and innovation; 
• Positively influence policy through assessment of regional RDI capacity and funding tools to mature EST for KT, ensuring cost-efficient exploitation of resources, so that best value for money on investment made by public & private bodies is achieved.

en.expected_outputs:
• Blue economy stakeholders engagement, identify needs & trends, pre-evaluation of EST market need; 
• Design risk assessment and cost effectiveness tools for Atlantic Area academia and public bodies in the Atlantic region o strength risk management systems; 
• Co-development of the Academia Innovation Enhancer tool to upgrade Academia skills for KT & innovation in blue economy sectors 
• Development of KT channels to market EST.
• Best-practices sharing through organization of joint events. 
• Influence improvements in public policy through assessment and recommendations of regional RDI capacity and funding tools to mature EST for commercialization, value creation and competitiveness increase for the Atlantic Area.

en.expected_results:
DiadES will positively impact diadromous fish management in the face of global climate change by:
 •	Fostering the necessary level of cooperation among Member States (MS) & actors involved in diadromous fish management to enable sound decision-making;
 •	Improving awareness and knowledge among policy makers and other key stakeholders on the services provided by these species and the need to set common management measures targeting both anthropogenic pressures & climate change;
 •	Favouring a joint promotion of ecosystem services related to diadromous fish in the AA to the wider public because they influence decision-making;
 •	Ensuring a sustainable ecosystem services provision by these species, combining exploitation & conservation, in support of AA local economies and quality of life.

en.expected_outputs:
• Capitalisation Plan implemented, aiming to achieve 42% of AA regions using the project outputs by 2023. Series of 7 Sustainability Plans produced, one per region;
• Common "cultural tourism ideas" Toolkit designed, developed and tested using 3 ideas in each region (21 across the 7 regions);
• Online Platform designed and operational, using the ideas generated to cooperatively develop and deliver new multi-region networked tourism packages. 
• “Multi-region” niche tourism packages piloted with tourists across the partner regions.
